.TH "xudc_dma_send" 9 "xudc_dma_send" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xudc_dma_send \- Sends IN data using DMA.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xudc_dma_send
.BI "(struct xusb_ep *ep "  ","
.BI "struct xusb_req *req "  ","
.BI "u8 *buffer "  ","
.BI "u32 length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
pointer to the usb device endpoint structure.
.IP "req" 12
pointer to the usb request structure.
.IP "buffer" 12
pointer to data to be sent.
.IP "length" 12
number of bytes to send.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -EAGAIN if no buffer is free and error
code on failure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function sends data using DMA.
